I’m riding a solar-powered electric moped 1,000 miles from Italy to Bulgaria, I tried towing a DIY solar trailer and relying only on portable solar panels to charge. This series documents my EV road trip, full of highs, lows, and real-time challenges — from solar charging and rainstorms to racing against time before my wife gives birth. Follow for
